  "wikitext": "\n'''6-6-240\n\nA switch in which the open-circuit state is produced automatically under given conditions.\n\n\nNote: 1 The device may also be used for manual operation under normal conditions.\n\n\nNote: 2 If the open-circuit state is produced sufficiently quickly to prevent the short-circuit current from attaining its full value, the term high-speed circuit breaker is applied.\n\n{{IALAFooter}}\n\n{{languages|Circuit breaker}}\n[[Category:6.6 Transmission of Electric Energy]]\n[[Category:Alphabetical Index]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 1970-89 Edition]]"
